00:04:51.079 --> 00:04:54.260
be, is, is very complex and is very diverse.

79
00:04:54.559 --> 00:04:58.380
Um, IT might reflect something of people's social situation

80
00:04:59.029 --> 00:05:03.500
that has become very difficult or their relational situation

81
00:05:03.920 --> 00:05:07.119
that has become very difficult. It might witness to

82
00:05:07.119 --> 00:05:10.700
very severe things that have happened in people's lives,

83
00:05:11.160 --> 00:05:14.540
or of course it might also. Uh, REVEAL something

84
00:05:14.540 --> 00:05:18.410
of an, of an internal dynamic. So, um, I

85
00:05:18.410 --> 00:05:20.940
don't know that on beforehand when as a psychoanalyst

86
00:05:20.940 --> 00:05:23.940
when I start working with people, but the key

87
00:05:23.940 --> 00:05:28.260
idea here is that it's not random, um, it's,

88
00:05:28.339 --> 00:05:33.260
it's psychotic experiences are responses to, to triggers, to,

89
00:05:33.390 --> 00:05:36.279
to situations that have been overwhelming for a person

90
00:05:36.500 --> 00:05:39.260
and as a psychoanalyst, I tend to stress this.

91
00:05:40.230 --> 00:05:43.679
And um that, that's of course a bit different

92
00:05:43.679 --> 00:05:48.670
compared to mainstream psychiatric practice where the idea is

