00:06:03.329 --> 00:06:06.609
it down, to kind of, to, to diminish the

98
00:06:06.609 --> 00:06:10.570
symptoms, to diminish the crisis experience that people have.

99
00:06:11.230 --> 00:06:14.829
And, and I'm not against medications, but for me

100
00:06:14.829 --> 00:06:19.269
the crisis experience is revelatory of something of, of

101
00:06:19.269 --> 00:06:22.750
how people live and how the challenges they are

102
00:06:22.750 --> 00:06:25.709
confronted with, and as a psychoanalyst, I want to

103
00:06:25.709 --> 00:06:29.750
value that component of the, of the psychotic experience.

104
00:06:30.820 --> 00:06:36.079
But do you still approach psychosis as a mental

105
00:06:36.859 --> 00:06:41.940
disease, um, and I mean, more broadly as a

106
00:06:41.940 --> 00:06:48.160
psychoanalyst, what is your understanding of what mental disease

107
00:06:48.160 --> 00:06:48.739
is?

108
00:06:49.059 --> 00:06:55.019
Yeah, so. Here I start from Freud and Sigmund

109
00:06:55.019 --> 00:06:59.829
Freud's opinion was that we actually all have psychopathological

110
00:06:59.829 --> 00:07:03.779
traits. Huh, a normal person does not exist. We

111
00:07:03.779 --> 00:07:07.739
all have our specific kinds of weirdness, huh, and

112
00:07:07.739 --> 00:07:10.980
so I see it as a dimension, huh, as,

113
00:07:11.070 --> 00:07:14.500
as a dimensional space in which you can have

114
00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:19.140
like very mild experiences of weirdness, uh, and that's

115
00:07:19.140 --> 00:07:22.679
what we usually call normal, but check normal people,

116
00:07:22.859 --> 00:07:25.179
it's not that they know who they are, it's

117
00:07:25.179 --> 00:07:28.980
not that they are always like very rational in

118
00:07:28.980 --> 00:07:32.839
what they do. Um, NORMAL people still have like

119
00:07:32.839 --> 00:07:36.989
all kinds of irrational thoughts. Um, THEY also suffer

120
00:07:36.989 --> 00:07:40.429
from doubts and uncertainties. They have weird dreams. They,

121
00:07:40.529 --> 00:07:42.829
they say stupid things to their partner, to their

122
00:07:42.829 --> 00:07:45.709
children. So even if you are, so to speak,

123
00:07:45.790 --> 00:07:50.329
normal, you have in Freudian perspective, you still are

124
00:07:50.480 --> 00:07:54.950
wrestling in a certain sense with like situating yourself

125
00:07:54.950 --> 00:07:57.630
in the world and in your, also with respect

126
00:07:57.630 --> 00:08:00.619
to your inner world. Um, BUT here the idea

127
00:08:00.619 --> 00:08:06.250
is that um we can. Move on that um

128
00:08:06.250 --> 00:08:10.179
dimension to the direction when things become a problem,

129
00:08:10.570 --> 00:08:14.970
when people start to experience these inner experiences or

130
00:08:14.970 --> 00:08:18.760
these relations to other people as potentially a problem.

131
00:08:19.049 --> 00:08:21.649
So when I doubt and I doubt a bit

132
00:08:21.649 --> 00:08:25.459
too much, Then maybe my life is troubled because

133
00:08:25.459 --> 00:08:29.260
I can't make decisions anymore or I, I start

