00:08:29.260 --> 00:08:32.739
feeling anxious or I start feeling depressed, so it's

135
00:08:32.739 --> 00:08:35.460
when it moves, when it becomes more extreme, it

136
00:08:35.460 --> 00:08:38.400
becomes a clinical problem and a clinical problem is

137
00:08:38.619 --> 00:08:41.940
a problem for which you need help because you

138
00:08:41.940 --> 00:08:45.099
can't cope with it anymore yourself. So for me

139
00:08:45.099 --> 00:08:48.419
that's a clinical situation, that's, so to speak, a

140
00:08:48.419 --> 00:08:53.159
disorder that, that is when the internal order. It's

141
00:08:53.159 --> 00:08:55.799
disruptive to such an extent that you can't cope

142
00:08:55.799 --> 00:08:59.039
with it on yourself anymore, huh, so that's my,

143
00:08:59.159 --> 00:09:01.719
my broad idea of what what what is a

144
00:09:01.719 --> 00:09:05.119
disorder or what is a clinical problem and, and

145
00:09:05.119 --> 00:09:08.200
here we have to apply that continuum also to

146
00:09:08.200 --> 00:09:12.599
the experience of psychosis, um. There's many people who

147
00:09:12.599 --> 00:09:16.150
at a certain point of their lives have um

148
00:09:16.450 --> 00:09:19.250
like experiences that are very difficult to explain to

