00:09:25.010 --> 00:09:28.450
some vague experiences of reality that is, that, that

151
00:09:28.450 --> 00:09:31.299
is strange in a certain sense, but that does

152
00:09:31.299 --> 00:09:34.369
not mean that it is a clinical problem, huh,

153
00:09:34.690 --> 00:09:37.460
but it can evolve in such a way. That

154
00:09:37.460 --> 00:09:40.700
it becomes a problem, that it becomes intolerable for

155
00:09:40.700 --> 00:09:43.859
yourself, or that people in your, in your environment

156
00:09:43.859 --> 00:09:47.219
like in your family start being worried about you

157
00:09:47.219 --> 00:09:50.200
because in their opinion, you're doing weird things or

158
00:09:50.210 --> 00:09:53.059
or having weird thoughts, so that's a point where

159
00:09:53.059 --> 00:09:56.299
it might become clinical and clinical means that it's.

160
00:09:56.599 --> 00:10:00.479
It implies uh um a severe degree of suffering,

161
00:10:01.059 --> 00:10:03.520
uh, so for me that's, that's the criterion. If

162
00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:06.789
something of an inner experience or an experience of

163
00:10:06.789 --> 00:10:10.760
reality is so disturbing that it creates real suffering

164
00:10:10.760 --> 00:10:13.960
for people, then it starts to be clinical and

165
00:10:13.960 --> 00:10:18.039
then it becomes a problem where clinicians, uh, should

